Stocks Pare Rally as Energy Shares Fall Back

-- B y   N i c k   B a k e r
-- 
2011-06-29T18:17:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-29/u-s-stocks-pare-gain-as-energy-financial-technology-shares-trim-advance.html
The  Standard & Poor’s  500 Index
pared its third straight gain, with energy, financial and
technology companies trimming their advance the most in the past
half hour.  The  S&P 500  climbed 0.6 percent to 1,304.22 at 2:16 p.m. in
 New York  after increasing as much as 1 percent after  Greece 
passed austerity measures, pending home sales climbed and
Monsanto Co.’s sales beat estimates.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
